-- 02_enrich_subscriptions.sql
```sql
SELECT
  s.subscription_id,
  s.user_id,
  s.plan_id,
  s.started_at,
  s.ended_at,
  s.status,
  p.tier,
  p.monthly_price,

FROM subscriptions s

-- 03_monthly_metrics_base.sql
```sql
WITH deduplicated_events AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
  FROM billing_events
),
enriched_subscriptions AS (
  SELECT
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.plan_id,
    s.started_at,
    s.ended_at,
    s.status,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(p.monthly_price, 0) AS monthly_price,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
)
SELECT
  de.event_month AS month,
  es.tier,
  es.industry,
  es.subscription_id,
  es.user_id,
  COALESCE(de.amount, es.monthly_price) AS revenue_amount
FROM deduplicated_events de
JOIN enriched_subscriptions es ON de.subscription_id = es.subscription_id;
```

-- 04_final_monthly_metrics.sql
```sql
WITH deduplicated_events AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
  FROM billing_events
),
enriched_subscriptions AS (
  SELECT
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.plan_id,
    s.started_at,
    s.ended_at,
    s.status,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(p.monthly_price, 0) AS monthly_price,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
),
monthly_data AS (
  SELECT
    de.event_month AS month,
    es.tier,
    es.industry,
    es.subscription_id,
    es.user_id,
    COALESCE(de.amount, es.monthly_price) AS revenue_amount
  FROM deduplicated_events de
  JOIN enriched_subscriptions es ON de.subscription_id = es.subscription_id
)
SELECT
  month,
  tier,
  industry,
  COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
  SUM(revenue_amount) AS total_mrr,
  COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM monthly_data
GROUP BY month, tier, industry
ORDER BY month, tier, industry;
